  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess the safety, tolerability and preliminary efficacy of
      a new drug aimed at controlling disease reactivation in patients diagnosed with primary
      haemophagocytic lymphohistiocytosis and having previously shown partial response to current
      recommended treatment. The new drug will be administered on top of a glucocorticosteroid,
      which is usually part of the current recommended treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
